        <updateDate>2020-03-23T16:22:11Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Decrease Noise Levels Act</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) to revise its regulations to decrease the threshold for the day-night average sound level that constitutes significant noise from 65 decibels to 60 decibels, and adjust relative ranges of day-night average sound level accordingly.</p> <p>Additionally, the FAA must</p> <ul> <li>ensure that its community outreach related to aviation day-night average sound levels contains the results of its evaluation of alternative metrics to the current average day-night level standard, and</li> <li>create a publicly available report that outlines a strategy to reduce the maximum day-night average sound level in all residential areas to 55 decibels within 10 years. </li> </ul>]]></text>
      </summary>
